Overload.descr:
Break [LoopLabel_OrLevel]

Example:

outer:
Loop 3
{
    x := A_Index
    Loop 3
    {
        if (x*A_Index = 6)
            break outer  ; Equivalent to break 2 or goto break_outer.
        MsgBox x ',' A_Index
    }
}
break_outer: ; For goto.

Data = Buffer obj
Size = number of bytes to use

Returns = obj{Ptr, Size}

Continue [LoopLabel_OrLevel]

Example:

    outer:
    Loop 3
    {
        x := A_Index
        Loop 3
        {
            if (x*A_Index = 4)
                continue outer  ; Equivalent to continue 2 or goto continue_outer.
            MsgBox x ',' A_Index
        }
        continue_outer: ; For goto.
    }

    try {
        ...
    } finally {
        ...
    }

-- OR --

    try {
        ...
    } catch [ErrorClass] [as ErrorObj] {
        ...
    } else {
        ...
    } finally {
        ...
    }

Must come after Try statement.

    For Value1 [, Value2] in Expression {
        ...
    }

Repeats one or more statements once for each key-value pair in an object.

Options: Xn Yn: X and Y coords of the InputBox gui. Wn Hn: W and H of the InputBox gui. T: Timeout in seconds. Password: Shows *** in edit box.
Returns obj{Value, Result}
Value = text entered by user Result = OK, Cancel, Timeout

Loop [Count] {
    Statements
}

Loop Vars: A_Index (common to all loops)

Switch [SwitchValue, CaseSense] {
    Case CaseValue1: Statements...
    Case CaseValue2: Statements...
    Default: Statements...
}

    try {
        ...
    } catch [ErrorClass] [as ErrorObj] {
        ...
    } else {
        ...
    } finally {
        ...
    }

-- OR --

    Try (Statement)

Used with Loop, While, and For loops.

    Loop [Count] {
        ...
    } Until (expression)

    For i, value in Array {
        ...
    } Until (expression)

-- OR --

    While (expression) {
        ...
    } Until (expression)

    While (expression) {
        ...
    }

-- OR --

    While (expression) {
        ...
    } Until (expression)
